{
  "Pitch": "Project Pollo is pioneering the fast-food industry as America's first vegan chicken fast-food chain, addressing the dilemma of consumers having to choose between affordable but questionable meat-based options and expensive, healthier alternatives. By offering a range of delicious and affordable plant-based options, Project Pollo makes healthier food more accessible to all Americans, regardless of income. The chain's menu boasts a hand-breaded crispy chicken patty made from 100% soy, along with an array of burgers, wraps, salads, shakes, and innovative items like Buffalo mac and cheese. With a mission to provide affordable plant-based food to all Americans, Project Pollo is poised to revolutionize the quick-serve restaurant landscape.",
  "Initial_Offer": {
    "Funding_Amount": "$2.5 million",
    "Equity_Offered": "5%",
    "Valuation": "$47.5 million",
    "Key_Terms": "First-mover advantage, growing demand for plant-based options, potential for rapid expansion"
  }
}

{
  "Pitch": "Pashion Footwear is revolutionizing the footwear industry with the world's first fully convertible high heels that can transform into comfortable flats with a simple twist. This innovative solution addresses the common problem of high-heel pain and discomfort experienced by women. By providing a stylish and comfortable alternative, Pashion Footwear aims to disrupt the market and capture a significant share of the footwear industry. With a strong growth potential and a large addressable market, Pashion Footwear is poised for significant growth and is seeking an investment to drive expansion and scale production.",
  "Initial_Offer": {
    "Funding_Amount": "$500,000",
    "Equity_Offered": "5%",
